p: \bPlease... just let me go back to my family!
\rNow, now...\nThere's no need to panic.\nI'm sure we can come to an agreeable conclusion.
\rWell, it has come to our attention that you have something we want.
\rSo just let us have it, and everything will be just fine, okay?
\bIf... if you're talking about the scroll we unearthed, we can't just hand it to you!
\bIt's important to us...\nMy children found it.\nThey would be really upset if I just gave it away.

I understand exactly where you're coming from.
That scroll must have sentimental value...
But what is more important to you?
How your children feel? Or
whether or not their hearts are beating?
\rThere are several explosives around the ladder behind you.\nYour two children are down there, I understand?
\rIf you do not give us the scroll, we'll blow it up.\nWe don't want to do it, but if you're not being cooperative... well, we won't have a choice.
\bWhat... what do you need it for?
\rWell, we're cultists. Sky Cultists, to be specific.\nAnd your scroll contains the words of the ritual necessary to summon Rayquaza.
\rNow, have you made your decision? You give us the scroll, and we'll let your family live.
\bPlease, take this. Stay away from my family.
\rVery well, we'll leave. Go warn your children.
\rNow that we have the scroll, we're heading to Helios City.\nWe'll use the Augur's energy to summon Rayquaza for us.
\bThe Augur's going to help us? Why would he do that?
\rI have a very good reason as to why he would want to help us, and if he doesn't, I'll be very angry.\nAnd as we've seen here, in this cave, we don't like
me when I'm angry.\nIn fact, just to prove my point... why you shouldn't anger me...
\rSorry, I've never been a fan of jokes that ended in puns.
\rDead men tell no tales. We can't have anyone knowing about the plans of Sky Cult until necessary.
This hole looks deep. I should probably stay away.
Battle: \rThis cave has plenty of valuable minerals.\nThat's why it attracts miners from all over the region!
EndSpeech: Maybe you should give it a try! It's really fun!
\rThis cave has plenty of valuable minerals.\nThat's why it attracts miners from all over the region!

EndSpeech: Sorry, I had to clear my throat.

Battle: \rI don't really understand why Pokemon fighting is legal... when you think about it, it's kind of unethical!
EndSpeech: I just don't get it...
\rI don't really understand why Pokemon fighting is legal... when you think about it, it's kind of unethical!
\bWhat a coincidence- I was actually just looking for you!
\bI've been training up all my Pokemon, and I've restyled my looks.
\bThey're based around my new partner, Shaymin!
\bI think I'm ready to take you on.\nI hope you're ready, because I'm not losing again!

\b\pn... the Sky Cult is no joke.
\bIf they're going to try to use the Jade Tower to summon Rayquaza, I have no doubt they can pull it off.
\bThe Augur has to be warned!\nThat's where he lives, after all.
